The Deputy Governor of Kogi State, Mr Simon Achuba, has been impeached. According to Vanguard, Mr Achuba was impeached by members of the Kogi State House of Assembly. This is coming after the judicial panel of enquiry set up by the Kogi State Chief Judge, Justice Nadir Ajanah, to investigate Achuba’s alleged gross misconduct submitted its report on Friday. Details later… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.